textBody:
IWW may refer to:

Organizations

*Industrial Workers of the World, known as the Wobblies, an international union founded in 1905
*Irish Whip Wrestling, an Irish-owned independent professional wrestling promotion established in 2002

Transport

*Inland waterway, a body of water, such as a river, canal or lake, is navigable if it is deep, wide and slow enough for a vessel to pass.

Music

*It Was Written, the second studio album by American rapper Nas
